{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀλάομαι</b> [ᾰλ], <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i><i>plural</i> ἀλόωνται, <i>imperative</i> ἀλόω (see. below), used by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus mostly in _contraction_ forms ἀλᾶσθε, ἀλώμενος, \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>imperfect</i> ἠλώμην, <i>Epic dialect</i> ἀλᾶτο: <i>future</i> ἀλήσομαι (ἀπ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 409\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] (variant{ἀπαλήσατο}): <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>aorist</i> ἀλήθην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.120, 362\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>participle</i> ἀλᾱθείς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 870: \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> ἀλάλημαι (which see): (ἄλη):—<b>wander, roam</b>, οἷά τε ληιστῆρες..τοί τ᾽ ἀλόωνται ψυχὰς παρθέμενοι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.73; ὅδε τις δύστηνος ἀλώμενος ἐνθάδ᾽ ἱκάνει 6.206; μὴ πάθωμέν τι ἀλώμενοι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.97; αἰσχρῶς ἀλῶμαι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 98\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἄσιτος νηλίπους τ᾽ ἀ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 349\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: especially <b>to be outcast, banished</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 444, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.102, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 6.30, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.310\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκσέθεν by thee, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1363: —frequently with Preps., ἀνὰ στρατὸν οἶοι ἀλᾶσθε 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.141; κὰπ πεδίον..οἶος ἀλᾶτο 6.201; πολλὰ βροτῶν ἐπὶ ἄστἐ ἀλώμενος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.492; γῆς ἐπ᾽ ἐσχάτοις ὅροις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 666; ἐπὶ ξένης χώρας 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 300, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.168; οὕτω νῦν..ἀλόω κατὰ πόντον 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.377, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 870; νομάδεσσι γὰρ ἐν Σκύθαις ἀλᾶται 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 942: with _accusative_ loci, ἀ. γῆν\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>wander over</b> the land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1686; πορθμοὺς ἀ. μυρίους 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 532; οὔρεα 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 13.66. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>wander away from, miss</b> a thing, εὐφροσύνας ἀλᾶται[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.58; ψυχὴν ἀλᾶται τῆς πάροιθ᾽ εὐπραξίας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 640. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>wander in mind, be perplexed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 23.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6215","accentedUnicode":"ἀλάομαι","shortDef":"be a runaway","mediumDef":"be a runaway","stepGloss":"be a runaway","stepTransliteration":"alaomai","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}